info.title: Google Analytics API
info.description: The Google Analytics Platform lets you measure user interactions with your business across various devices and environments, at Google speed and scale. Gain new insights and optimize the performance of your business.

parameters.name: callback
parameters.description: Name of the JavaScript callback function that handles the response. Used in JavaScript JSON-P requests.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of ad units to include in the response, used for paging. The minimum value is 0 (zero) and the maximum value is 10000 (10 thousand). Default is 10000 (10 thousand).

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: A continuation token, used to page through ad units. To retrieve the next page, set this parameter to the value of nextPageToken from the previous response. Default returns the first page of results.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.description: Returns the response in a human-readable format (with indentations and line breaks) if true. When this is false, it can reduce the response payload size, which might lead to better performance in some environments. Default value: false.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.description: Lets you enforce per-user quotas from a server-side application even in cases when the users IP address is unknown. This can occur, for example, with applications that run cron jobs on App Engine on a users behalf. You can choose any arbitrary string that uniquely identifies a user, but it is limited to 40 characters. Alternative to userIp, overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.description: IP address of the end user for whom the API call is being made. Lets you enforce per-user quotas when calling the API from a server-side application.

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description: Account on which to report.

parameters.name: currency
parameters.description: Not available.

parameters.name: dimension
parameters.description: Optional dimensions on which to base the report.Available dimensions are:- DATE- WEEK- MONTH- AD_CLIENT_ID- PRODUCT_CODE- PRODUCT_NAME- AD_UNIT_ID- AD_UNIT_CODE- AD_UNIT_NAME- AD_UNIT_SIZE_CODE- AD_UNIT_SIZE_NAME- CUSTOM_CHANNEL_ID- CUSTOM_CHANNEL_CODE- CUSTOM_CHANNEL_NAME- URL_CHANNEL_ID- URL_CHANNEL_NAME- AD_FORMAT_CODE- AD_FORMAT_NAME- BRANDING_TYPE_CODE- BRANDING_TYPE_NAME- BUYER_NETWORK_ID- BUYER_NETWORK_NAME- BID_TYPE_CODE- BID_TYPE_NAME- DOMAIN_NAME- COUNTRY_CODE- COUNTRY_NAME- TARGETING_

parameters.name: endDate
parameters.description: End of the date range on which to report in YYYY-MM-DD format, inclusive.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: Selector specifying a subset of fields to include in the response. Use for better performance.

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: Set of filters to be applied to the report.

parameters.name: locale
parameters.description: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local language. Defaults to en_US if not specified.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of rows of report data to return. The minumum value is 0 (zero), the maximum value is 50000 (50 thousand).

parameters.name: metric
parameters.description: Optional numeric columns to include in the report.Available metrics are:- PAGE_VIEWS- PAGE_VIEWS_CTR- PAGE_VIEWS_RPM- AD_REQUESTS- AD_REQUESTS_COVERAGE- AD_REQUESTS_CTR- AD_REQUESTS_RPM- MATCHED_AD_REQUESTS- MATCHED_AD_REQUESTS_CTR- MATCHED_AD_REQUESTS_RPM- INDIVIDUAL_AD_IMPRESSIONS- INDIVIDUAL_AD_IMPRESSIONS_CTR- INDIVIDUAL_AD_IMPRESSIONS_RPM- CLICKS- EARNINGS- TOTAL_EARNINGS- COST_PER_CLICK

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.description: Returns the response in a human-readable format (with indentations and line breaks) if true. When this is false, it can reduce the response payload size, which might lead to better performance in some environments. Default value: false.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.description: Lets you enforce per-user quotas from a server-side application even in cases when the users IP address is unknown. This can occur, for example, with applications that run cron jobs on App Engine on a users behalf. You can choose any arbitrary string that uniquely identifies a user, but it is limited to 40 characters. Alternative to userIp, overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: Optional name of a dimension or metric on which to sort the resulting report. Optionally prefixed with + to sort ascending or - to sort descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted ascending:- DATE- WEEK- MONTH- AD_CLIENT_ID- PRODUCT_CODE- PRODUCT_NAME- AD_UNIT_ID- AD_UNIT_CODE- AD_UNIT_NAME- AD_UNIT_SIZE_CODE- AD_UNIT_SIZE_NAME- CUSTOM_CHANNEL_ID- CUSTOM_CHANNEL_CODE- CUSTOM_CHANNEL_NAME- URL_CHANNEL_ID- URL_CHANNEL_NAME- AD_FORMAT_CODE- AD_FORMAT_NAME- BRANDING_TYPE_CODE- BRANDI

parameters.name: startDate
parameters.description: Start of the date range on which to report in YYYY-MM-DD format, inclusive.

parameters.name: startIndex
parameters.description: Index of the first row of report data to return. The minumum value is 0 (zero), the maximum value is 5000 (5 thousand). If startIndex is either unset or zero, the API will return as many rows as specified by the value of maxResults. If maxResults is not set the API will return as many rows as possible, up to 50,000. If startIndex is set to a non-zero value, the sum of startIndex and maxResults cannot be greater than 5000, or an error will be returned: paging past row 5000 is unsupported.
